gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Jazz 154, Pistons 148
gameRecap.excerpt: The Jazz defeated the Pistons, 154-148, in overtime. Jordan Clarkson led the way for the Jazz with 36 points (4-5 3PT FG) and six rebounds, while Lauri Markkanen added 30 points (4-8 3PT FG) and six rebounds in the victory. Bojan Bogdanovic tallied a season-high 36 points (8-15 3PT FG), along with seven rebounds and five assists for the Pistons in the losing effort. The Jazz have won three consecutive games as they improve to 16-19 on the season, while the Pistons fall to 3-31.
